COMMENT ON TABLE REFERENCE_DOMAINS IS 'Maintains domains or groupings for many setup codes (simple code tables).';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.DOMAIN IS 'The code used to uniquely identify the reference domain.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.PARENT_DOMAIN IS 'The parent domain of this domain, used for modelling parent/child (hierachically structured) code tables.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.SUPER_SET_DOMAIN IS 'Controls the consistent use of codes where the same code is required in more than one domain, through holding all such codes in a master domain called a superset. Where a code must be in multiple domains, a superset domain holds all related codes, with the other domains selecting codes from the superset. Example:  2 domains for gender codes: - Domain 1 [personâ€™s gender]:  valid codes are MALE and FEMALE - Domain 2 [gender(s) a programme can accept.]  valid codes MALE, FEMALE and BOTH. The superset domain holds all possible gender-related codes (MALE, FEMALE, BOTH), and the codes for domains 1 and 2 are drawn from this superset.)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.APPLN_CODE IS 'The code used to identify the application area that the reference domain pertains to, e.g., Trust, Commissary, CTAG etc. Ref Domain ( APPLN )';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.DESCRIPTION IS 'Description of the reference domain';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.DOMAIN_STATUS IS 'The status of the reference domain. Ref Domain ( DOMAIN_STS )';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.OWNER_CODE IS 'The identity of the owner of the reference domain. Ref Domain ( USER_CLS ). Indicative of the party who has rights to modify the codes.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.CODE_LENGTH IS 'No longer used.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.OLD_CODE_TABLE IS 'No longer used.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.CREATE_DATETIME IS 'The timestamp when the record was created';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.CREATE_USER_ID IS 'The user account that created the record';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.MODIFY_DATETIME IS 'The timestamp when the record was last modified ';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.MODIFY_USER_ID IS 'The user account that last modified the record';
COMMENT ON COLUMN REFERENCE_DOMAINS.SEAL_FLAG IS 'Flag to indicate whether the record has been sealed or not (Y/N).';
COMMENT ON TABLE SYSTEM_EVENTS IS 'Maintains list of key dates when certain events will take place. For example: it is used in Payroll to define holidays when offenders are not expected to work.';
